<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>赛琪 |关于人类状况</title><link>https://psyche.co</link><description>Psyche 是 Aeon 的一本数字杂志，通过心理学、哲学和艺术阐明人类状况。</description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 06 Nov 2023 06:15:04 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>饭纲博览会</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/get-lost-in-enigmatic-memories-of-a-small-town-japanese-fair?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/b881593e-78e7-4d24-8d63-15b72177a25e/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;这部引人入胜的动画唤起了模糊的记忆和徒劳的遗憾，讲述了一个在日本陷入沉思的男人的故事&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/get-lost-in-enigmatic-memories-of-a-small-town-japanese-fair?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Nov 2023 10:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/get-lost-in-enigmatic-memories-of-a-small-town-japanese-fair?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为什么口语诗不仅仅是诗歌朗诵</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/why-spoken-word-poetry-is-so-much-more-than-a-poetry-reading?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="一名男子在俱乐部活动中打手势并背诵诗歌" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/c67db614-97f2-4de7-8d29-4afa6700ee6e/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;随着诗歌回归其作为表演艺术的根源，它为许多人提供了强大的治疗和社区来源&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——艾丽卡·弗莱彻&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/why-spoken-word-poetry-is-so-much-more-than-a-poetry-reading?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Nov 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/why-spoken-word-poetry-is-so-much-more-than-a-poetry-reading?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如何在“冒名顶替综合症”中茁壮成长</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-move-beyond-imposter-syndrome-and-thrive?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="通勤者冲过静止的通勤列车。火车窗外倒映着悉尼海港大桥" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/8906f346-e0b0-4d66-8002-bf2466c36e93/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;对自己无能和不值得的担忧可能会阻碍你。尝试以下步骤，迈向你想要的生活&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——吉尔·斯托达德&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-move-beyond-imposter-syndrome-and-thrive?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Nov 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-move-beyond-imposter-syndrome-and-thrive?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>异教是爱尔兰保护运动的强大力量</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/paganism-is-a-potent-force-in-irelands-conservation-movement?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/16ea5cf4-8079-40f9-8992-bce29f5b68f8/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;长期以来对愤怒仙女居住的“另一个世界”的信仰现在正在推动爱尔兰生态活动的复兴&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 朱朱巷&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/paganism-is-a-potent-force-in-irelands-conservation-movement?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/paganism-is-a-potent-force-in-irelands-conservation-movement?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>聆听恐怖：为什么许多女性喜欢真实犯罪播客</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/listening-in-on-horror-why-many-women-love-true-crime-podcasts?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="雨夜，一位表情沉思的女士在公交车上听耳机" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/d6d41d21-ed65-4357-a882-78dbf57e48bb/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;真实犯罪播客将针对女性的暴力行为变成了一种娱乐形式。为什么这么多女性听众喜欢它们？&lt;p&gt; &lt;em&gt;——阿米莉亚·安东尼&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/listening-in-on-horror-why-many-women-love-true-crime-podcasts?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 30 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/listening-in-on-horror-why-many-women-love-true-crime-podcasts?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>心依然嗡嗡作响</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/706a0e80-e38b-43ab-ad6e-8c9edf1db1a4/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;温柔地审视五位面临巨大困难的母亲，她们开始打破毒瘾、贫困和忽视的循环&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Oct 2023 10:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/stories-of-mothers-in-crisis-form-a-poignant-portrait-of-unconditional-love?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>在充满尼安德特人骨骼的洞穴中挖掘答案</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="在洞穴地面上挖掘的浮雕中可以看到头骨的骨骼轮廓" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/9ed85d80-8a3d-44e1-a3db-128c02bb1398/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;当一组研究人员返回一个被认为是尼安德特人埋葬地的伊拉克洞穴时，他们发现了以下内容&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——莎拉·爱&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/digging-for-answers-in-a-cave-filled-with-neanderthal-skeletons?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如何克服数学焦虑</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-beat-maths-anxiety-and-even-find-you-enjoy-it?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://epsilon.aeon.co/images/9cd1d819-0617-4a24-9d7d-ce3e678bca7b/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;对数学感到压力是很常见的，但没有必要。只要采取正确的方法，您甚至可以开始享受它&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——莎拉·爱&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-beat-maths-anxiety-and-even-find-you-enjoy-it?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-beat-maths-anxiety-and-even-find-you-enjoy-it?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如果思考是理性的，那么是什么让过度思考变得非理性呢？</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/if-thinking-is-rational-what-makes-overthinking-irrational?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="从后面看到一位女士一边打电话一边心不在焉地用手梳理着头发" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/e9977038-e9aa-4b85-bdf4-6c3e63b6c448/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;关于过度思考的哲学视角为焦虑和强迫症所涉及的心理过程提供了新的见解&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——巴勃罗·胡巴赫·哈尔勒&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/if-thinking-is-rational-what-makes-overthinking-irrational?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/if-thinking-is-rational-what-makes-overthinking-irrational?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为什么当你能在艺术中看到自己时，艺术看起来更美丽</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/5611e3e8-feae-429e-b262-4f0d569b64cb/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;研究表明，当艺术品在某种程度上与个人相关时，人们会觉得艺术品更美观&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——马特·休斯顿&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 23 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item></channel></rss>